response.overview: The Royal Nova Scotia International Tattoo 2016 was a spectacular showcase of military and civilian performances held in Halifax, Nova Scotia, from June 30 to July 7, 2016. This annual event featured a diverse array of acts, including military bands, acrobats, dancers, and drill teams from various countries, celebrating international culture and camaraderie.
response.tagline: Experience the world on stage: A spectacular fusion of military precision and cultural artistry.
response.title: Royal Nova Scotia International Tattoo - 2016
